Subject: fix for MOBO ethernet port hardware hand when under pressure
Cruise: AT WHOI 2017
Attachment: 
Encoding: HTML
========================================
<p>Put the following in ftp:/etc/rc.local as the last thing to do. There seemed to be several different ways to do this, but they all seemed rather convoluted (hard to find). If some barfs early on in rc.local this will not get run.&nbsp;</p>

<p># run ethtool on interfaces to fix hardware resets</p>

<p>/sbin/ethtool -K eth0 gso off gro off tso off</p>

<p>/sbin/ethtool -K eth1 gso off gro off tso off</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>ethtool --show-offload&nbsp; eth0</p>

<p>will show if the above is on or off.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>One of the better articles:</p>

<p><a href="http://www.linuxhelp.in/2017/02/how-to-enable-disable-offload-tso-gso-sg-tx-rx-checksum.html" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">http://www.linuxhelp.in/2017/02/how-to-enable-disable-offload-tso-gso-sg-tx-rx-checksum.html</a><br />
